# Copy to .publish-guard.local (gitignored) and list ERE regex patterns, one
# per line, that must never appear in a committed file. The pre-commit hook
# (scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit) reads this file. Blank lines and #-comments
# are ignored. These are YOUR machine specifics — keep them out of the tree.
#
# Examples (replace with your own; do NOT commit the real values):
# /Users/yourname
# /home/yourname
# op://your-private-vault
# your-github-username
# you@example\.com
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Publish gate (separate mechanism — configured via `git config`, NOT here):
#   git config publishguard.publicmatch  'YOUR_ORG/YOUR_REPO'   # required
#   git config publishguard.publicremote 'YOUR_PUBLIC_REMOTE'   # required
#   git config publishguard.publishbranch 'publish'             # required
#   git config publishguard.privateremote 'origin'              # optional
#   git config publishguard.sentinel     'PUBLISH_GUARD_OK'     # optional
# scripts/install-guards.sh wires the `git publish` alias from these and the
# pre-push hook fails closed: a direct push of the default branch to the
# public remote is blocked unless it comes via `git publish` (which backs up
# to the private remote first). Deliberate override: git push --no-verify
